<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Has_key on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/has_key/</link><description>Recent content in Has_key on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/has_key/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Python dict.has_key() Deprecated — Use 'in' Operator</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/python/has-key/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/python/has-key/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-python-dicthas_key-deprecated--use-in-operator"&gt;[Solution] Python dict.has_key() Deprecated — Use &amp;lsquo;in&amp;rsquo; Operator&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;dict.has_key()&lt;/code&gt; method was deprecated in Python 2.6 and removed in Python 3. The preferred way to check for key existence in a dictionary is the &lt;code&gt;in&lt;/code&gt; operator, which is more Pythonic, readable, and consistent with other container types in Python.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-youll-see"&gt;What You&amp;rsquo;ll See&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you run Python 2 code with &lt;code&gt;has_key()&lt;/code&gt; under Python 3:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-python" data-lang="python"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;config &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; {&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;host&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;localhost&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;port&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;8080&lt;/span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; config&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;has_key(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;host&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;):
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; print(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Host found&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;You get:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>